RST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Feminine form of the old Roman family name   Julius .  A woman called Julia is mentioned in Paul's Epistle to the Romans (Romans 16:15), and the name was borne by numerous early saints. Its frequency increased with the vogue for classical names in the 18th century, and it continues to enjoy considerable popularity, although the recent introduction of   Julie   to the English-speaking world has reduced this somewhat. Well-known bearers include the British actress  Julia Foster  (  b. 1941 ) and American actress  Julia Roberts  (  b. 1967  as  Julie Fiona Roberts )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Julia O'Cromin was born about 1330, in Ireland. She had at least 1 son with Donald Glas I Maccarthy. She died in her hometown."},"et":{"ABT 1330–":"umbes 1330–Surnud","1320–1366":"1320–1366","1340–1414":"1340–1414","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1414":"1414","ABT 1330":"umbes 1330","1366":"1366","1320":"1320","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Ireland":"Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Iirimaa","Ireland":"Iirimaa"},"fi":{"ABT 1330–":"noin 1330–Kuollut","1320–1366":"1320–1366","1340–1414":"1340–1414","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1414":"1414","ABT 1330":"noin 1330","1366":"1366","1320":"1320","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Ireland":"Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Irlanti","Ireland":"Irlanti"},"fr":{"ABT 1330–":"environ 1330–Décédée","1320–1366":"1320–1366","1340–1414":"1340–1414","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","1414":"1414","ABT 1330":"environ 1330","1366":"1366","1320":"1320","1330":"1330","1340":"1340","Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Ireland":"Kilbrittain Castle, County Cork, Irlande","Ireland":"Irlande","lifeSummary":"Julia O'Cromin est née environ 1330, à Irlande. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Donald Glas I Maccarthy. Elle est décédée dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"ABT 1330–":"um 1330–Verstorben","1320–